President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump have announced their special guests for the President's first State of the Union address. The guests include Corey Adams, a skilled welder who will use his extra money from tax reform to invest in his daughters' education savings. Elizabeth Alvarado, Robert Mickens, Evelyn Rodriguez, and Freddy Cuevas, who are the parents of two girls who were brutally murdered by MS-13 gang members. Corporal (Ret.) Matthew Bradford, the first blind, double amputee to reenlist in the Marine Corps after being injured in Iraq. Jon Bridgers, the founder of the Cajun Navy 2016, a non-profit organization that provides aid during natural disasters. David Dahlberg, a fire prevention technician who saved 62 children and staff members from a wildfire. Officer Ryan Holets, who adopted a baby from parents suffering from opioid addiction. Ashlee Leppert, a Coast Guard technician who rescued Americans during the hurricane season. Agent Celestino "CJ" Martinez, a Special Agent for Homeland Security Investigations who has worked to dismantle criminal organizations like MS-13. Staff Sergeant Justin Peck, who saved the life of Chief Petty Officer Kenton Stacy during a mission in Syria. Preston Sharp, who has organized the placement of American flags and flowers on veterans' graves. And siblings Steve Staub and Sandy Keplinger, who have seen growth in their manufacturing company thanks to the tax cuts and reform legislation.